Gov. Bev Perdue on Wednesday joined health leaders from across North Carolina to attend President Barack Obamaâs health care forum at Broughton High School in Raleigh. The governor invited representatives from the stateâs leading health care organizations, including hospitals, research institutions, advocates and minority groups, to attend the event with her.
